caption: This is a stone statue of French Pierre Corneille (1606-84) is situated just beside The Pantheon. It is the work of sculptor Georges Rispail (1952) replacing an earlier bronze statue of Corneille that was melted down during the Vichy Regime.  What you see is Corneille mostly covered by cloak and peering forward while clutching a manuscript in his left hand. It is an interesting statue worth a quick look-see if passing through the area and interested in monument viewing.
Located with place du Pantheon stands a stone statue dedicated to the french dramatist Pierre Corneille, created by the sculptor Georges Rispail, its location is a lovely area to hang out in.
The statue is next to The Pantheon. It could do with a clean. He was a famous French dramatist.
Located right next to the pantheon, this stone statue of the Frenchman Pierre Corneille (1606-84), is considered one of the best writers of the French language and universal literature.
